Senator Britt
1 moves to amend the bill on page 1, line 5, by inserting the following at the end of the line and
2 before the period:
3
4 "AND TO INCREASE THE PUNISHMENT FOR COMMITTING AN ASSAULT WITH A
5 FIREARM AGAINST CERTAIN EMERGENCY, MEDICAL, AND LAW
6 ENFORCEMENT PERSONNEL";
7
8 and on page 6, lines 35-36, by inserting the following between the lines:
9
10 "SECTION 9.1.(a) G.S. 14-34.5 reads as rewritten:
11 "§ 14-34.5. Assault with a firearm on a law enforcement, probation, or parole officer, or
12 on a member of the North Carolina National Guard, or on a person employed at
13 a State or local detention facility.
14 (a) Any person who commits an assault with a firearm upon a law enforcement officer,
15 probation officer, or parole officer while the officer is in the performance of his or her duties is
16 guilty of a Class D felony.
17 (a1) Any person who commits an assault with a firearm upon a member of the North
18 Carolina National Guard while the member is in the performance of his or her duties is guilty of
19 a Class D felony.
20 (b) Anyone who commits an assault with a firearm upon a person who is employed at a
21 detention facility operated under the jurisdiction of the State or a local government while the
22 employee is in the performance of the employee's duties is guilty of a Class D felony.any of the
23 following persons who are in the performance of their duties is guilty of a Class B1 felony:
24 (1) A law enforcement officer.
25 (2) A probation officer.
26 (3) A parole officer.
27 (4) A member of the North Carolina National Guard.
28 (5) An employee of a detention facility operated under the jurisdiction of the State
29 or a local government.
30 (6) An emergency medical technician or other emergency health care provider.
31 (7) A medical responder.
32 (8) A firefighter.
